<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Griscom</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-10-23"><hi rend="italic">October 23,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Reports that he is informed by the minister of finance and leader of the
                            Chamber of Deputies that the Brazilian tariff law will not be altered
                            during the Congress now in session. It is intended to postpone for a
                            year the consideration of the tariff already begun.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>